III- Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS

KCCAns:
For cultivation of bitter gourd, land should be selected, in which the percentage of acid and salt should not be more than normal, ie, the PH of the land. Between 6.5 to 8.00 percent and the percentage of plant species in the soil should be more than enough so that adequate nutrients are available to the plants.

While preparing the field for the cultivation of bitter gourd, put 200 liters of biogas slurry or 2000 liters of organic fertilizers in the field and cultivate the soil with a halal after 4-5 days. After that leave the field open for one week. After that, plow three or four times a day by planting it with Manda (Patella) and adjust the field by making it 1 feet thick and 2 feet wide on the interval of 3 to 3 feet and add 500 grams of Vermi compost and 50 grams of copper sulphate powder Mix 200 grams ash and fill the thawal with soil and irrigate the fields. After 5-6 days of irrigation, sow the seeds sown in the fields. When sowing, add 4 to 5 seeds to each plant in the plant.

KCCAns: The fertilizer is to be made from the waste, from which the pieces of glass and metal pieces are separated properly and after this, the platform of 10x4 feet is prepared to prepare the Vermi compost up to 6 to 12 inches high. 2 ridges are added to this platform and huts are made for shade above the platform. Dry fodder on top of platform, fertilize 3-4 quintals of cow dung and 7-8 quintals of garbage (Garvage) Which gets irrigated by sail for 10-15 days so that the temperature of the compost can be reduced. After this, 100 thousand square feet are left to the extent of 10 thousand earthworms. After leaving the ketchu, the stitches are covered with jute sacks, and they keep irrigation for 4 days so that 45-50 percent moisture is maintained. Keep in mind that due to excessive wetness the air will be blocked and the microbes and earthworms will not be able to die or work.

KCCAns:
Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

Applying sick plant plants in the main field affects the production. The time for the nursery to be inserted is from May 15 to June 20. Prepare the nursery as per the prescribed schedule. Focus on the following points.
1. The seedlings produced from nursery of 800-1000 sqm are sufficient for one hectare area.
2. Treat the seeds with solution of salt and make 10 grams of Bavistin, 1 gram Streptocyclin solution in 10 liters of water.
3. Sprink the treated seeds and sow it in the nursery.
4. 5 cm Sprinkle seed sprouts evenly in a nursery filled with water.
5. During nursery preparation, add 8-12 kg dung manure 8-20 kg urea, 10-20 kg of single super phosphate, 5-6 kg of mutant of potash and 2-5 kg ??zinc sulphate per 1000 sq. M. Nursery.
